{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/stringchunk"]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StringChunk"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"String chunks are used to store groups of strings. Memory is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"allocated in blocks, and as strings are added to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStringChunk"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"they are copied into the next free position in a block. When a block"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is full a new block is allocated."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When storing a large number of strings, string chunks are more","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"efficient than using [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.strdup"},{"type":"text","text":"] since fewer calls to "},{"code":"malloc()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are needed, and less memory is wasted in memory allocation overheads."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By adding strings with [method"},{"code":"GLib.StringChunk.insert_const","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] it is also"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"possible to remove duplicates."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStringChunk"},{"type":"text","text":" use [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.StringChunk.new"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To add strings to a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStringChunk"},{"text":" us